AN ACT relating to domestic relations; prohibiting a court from
ordering a child to enroll or participate in a family
reunification treatment, program or service under certain
circumstances; requiring the Court Administrator to
arrange for the giving of instruction in certain courses
designed for the training of certain persons who are
involved in child custody proceedings or proceedings
relating to domestic violence; requiring the Court
Administrator to prepare and submit an annual report
concerning the instruction; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides that it is the policy of this State to: (1) ensure that minor
2 children have a continuing relationship with both parents after the parents have
3 ended their relationship; (2) encourage such parents to share the rights and
4 responsibilities of child rearing; and (3) establish that such parents have an
5 equivalent duty to provide their minor children with necessary maintenance, care,
6 education and support. (NRS 125C.001) Section 2 of this bill: (1) defines the term
7 “family reunification treatment, program or service” to mean a treatment, program
8 or service intended to facilitate or encourage a relationship between a child and an
9 estranged or rejected parent or other immediate member of the family of the child;
10 and (2) prohibits a court from ordering a child to enroll or participate in a family
11 reunification treatment, program or service under certain circumstances.
12 Existing law requires the Court Administrator, at the direction of the Chief
13 Justice of the Supreme Court, to arrange for the giving of instruction in certain
14 courses designed for the training of judges. (NRS 3.027) Section 3 of this bill
15 likewise: (1) requires the Court Administrator to arrange for the giving of
16 instruction in a course designed for the training of judges and certain other persons
17 who regularly and routinely interact with persons who are involved in child custody
