THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 125C of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, a
4 court shall not order a child to enroll or participate in a family
5 reunification treatment, program or service that, as a condition of
6 enrollment or participation, requires or results in:
7 (a) The issuance of an order prohibiting contact between the
8 child and a member of his or her immediate family;
9 (b) The child staying at a place other than his or her home
10 overnight or leaving this State;
11 (c) The transfer of legal custody or physical custody of the
12 child;
13 (d) The use or threatened use of force, physical obstruction,
14 intimidation, coercion or verbal abuse; or
15 (e) The isolation of the child from his or her family or
16 community.
17 2. As used in this section, “family reunification treatment,
18 program or service” means a treatment, program or service
19 intended to facilitate or encourage a relationship between a child
20 and an estranged or rejected parent or other member of his or her
21 immediate family. The term includes, without limitation, a
22 treatment, program or service provided by a camp, workshop,
23 therapeutic vacation or educational program.
24 Sec. 3. 1. The Court Administrator shall arrange for the
25 giving of instruction, at the National Council of Juvenile and
26 Family Court Judges in Reno, Nevada, or elsewhere, in a course
27 designed to improve the ability of a court to:
28 (a) Recognize and respond to child abuse, domestic violence
29 and trauma in a manner that is culturally sensitive and
30 appropriate for diverse communities; and
31 (b) Make child custody decisions that prioritize the safety and
32 well-being of children.
33 2. The instruction required by subsection 1 must:
34 (a) Be made available to judges and other persons who, during
35 the scope of their employment, have regular and routine contact
36 with persons who are involved in child custody proceedings or
